Class Subtask01

  • java.lang.Object
    • ua.khpi.hrynevych.task03.subtask01.Subtask01

  • public class Subtask01
extends java.lang.Object
    Class containing methods for converting input data that match the format "Login;Name;Email\n".
    Version:
    1.0, 17 Nov 2017
    Author:
    Hrynevych Pavlo

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Static Methods Instance Methods Concrete Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      java.lang.String convert1()
      Returns result in which for every user there is a line containing login and email that corresponds to it.
      java.lang.String convert2()
      Returns result in which for every user there is a line containing surname and name of the user (in such sequence) and his or her email.
      java.lang.String convert3()
      Returns result in which for every domain from the input data there is a line containing logins of all users, whose emails are registered in this domain.
      java.lang.String convert4()
      Returns result which is the same as input data with the exception of the new column with passwords for every user.
      private static java.lang.String generatePassword()
      Randomly generates password containing only digits.
